# Windsurf/Cursor AI Rules for LittleLegend

## Project Context
LittleLegend is a Next.js app that helps parents track their child's achievements from birth to adulthood, creating a timeline that transforms into a professional CV.

## Technology Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- React 18
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Lucide React (icons)

## Code Style Guidelines

### File Structure
- Pages: `src/app/[route]/page.tsx`
- Components: `src/components/[category]/ComponentName.tsx`
- Utilities: `src/lib/utils.ts`
- Types: Define inline or in `src/types/index.ts`

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `ActivityCard.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `handleSubmit`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `API_BASE_URL`)
- Files: kebab-case for pages, PascalCase for components

### TypeScript Rules
- Always use TypeScript
- Define interfaces for props
- Use strict mode
- Avoid `any` type

### Styling Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS classes exclusively
- Follow mobile-first approach
- Use custom colors from tailwind.config.ts:
  - royal-purple (primary)
  - legend-gold (secondary)
  - growth-green (success)
  - cream-50 (background)

### Component Patterns
```tsx
// Use function declarations for components
export default function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) {
  return (
    <div className="tailwind-classes">
      {/* content */}
    </div>
  );
}

// Export types with components
export interface ComponentNameProps {
  prop1: string;
  prop2?: number;
}
```

### Form Handling
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect)
- Client components with "use client" directive
- Handle loading states
- Show error messages

### Icons
- Use Lucide React: `import { IconName } from "lucide-react"`
- Common icons: Star, Plus, User, Settings, Trophy, Calendar

### Color Usage
- Primary buttons: `bg-royal-purple-700 text-white`
- Secondary buttons: `border-2 border-royal-purple-700 text-royal-purple-700`
- Cards: `bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg`
- Background: `bg-cream-50`

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile
- `md:` for tablets
- `lg:` for desktop
- Use `max-w-7xl mx-auto` for container width

## Common Tasks

### Creating a New Page
1. Create folder: `src/app/[route]/`
2. Create `page.tsx`
3. Add to navigation if needed
4. Use layout.tsx for shared UI

### Creating a Component
1. Create file: `src/components/[category]/ComponentName.tsx`
2. Define props interface
3. Export component
4. Import where needed

### Adding an Icon
1. Import from lucide-react
2. Use size classes: `w-5 h-5` for standard, `w-6 h-6` for large

### Styling a Button
- Primary: `bg-royal-purple-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-semibold hover:bg-royal-purple-800`
- Secondary: `border-2 border-royal-purple-700 text-royal-purple-700 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-semibold hover:bg-royal-purple-50`

### Creating a Card
```tsx
<div className="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-gray-100">
  {/* content */}
</div>
```

## Project-Specific Rules

### LittleLegend Brand
- Tagline: "Where every legend begins"
- Tone: Empowering, warm, professional but friendly
- Use emoji sparingly for kid-friendly sections

### Key Features to Remember
1. Track activities by category (Sports, Arts, Academic, etc.)
2. Upload photos/certificates
3. Timeline view
4. CV generation
5. Multiple children support

### Mock Data Structure
```typescript
interface Child {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  age: number;
  avatar: string;
  totalActivities: number;
}

interface Activity {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  category: string;
  date: string;
  icon: string;
}
```

## Commands
- Run dev: `npm run dev`
- Build: `npm run build`
- Type check: `npx tsc --noEmit`

## When Asked to Implement
1. Check existing files first
2. Follow the patterns shown in existing code
3. Use the color system defined in tailwind.config.ts
4. Make it responsive (mobile-first)
5. Add proper TypeScript types
6. Use Lucide icons
7. Follow the design in DESIGN.md

## Questions?
- Refer to DESIGN.md for UI specifications
- Refer to ARCHITECTURE.md for technical details
- Refer to WINDSURF.md for project overview
